nava: We are betraide, come my Lords, and let us goe tell the King of this.
capt: Well  ,  then  ,   I see you are resolute.
lor1: Now sirra, what shall we doe with the Admirall?
O no, his bodye will infect the fire, and the fire the aire, and so we shall be poysoned with him.
Lets throw him into the river.
Then throw him into the ditch.

mess: And it please your Majestie heere is a Frier of the order of the Jacobins, sent from the President of Paris, that craves accesse unto your grace.
murd2: O that his heart were leaping in my hand.
Shed your bloud, O Lord no: for we entend to strangle you.
poth: See where they be my  good   Lord, and he that smelles but to them, dyes.
I am my Lord, in what your grace commaundes till death.
Maddame, I beseech your grace to except this simple gift.
sero: Husband come down, heer's one would speak with you from the Duke of Guise .
frie:
My Lord, I come to bring you newes, that your brother the Cardinall of Loraine by the Kings consent is 
lately strangled unto death.
My Lord, heare me but speak  .  ,   I am a Frier of the order of the Jacobyns, that for my conscience sake will kill the King.
O my Lord, I have beene a great sinner in my dayes, and the deed is meritorious.
murd1: Feare him said you? tush, were he heere, we would kill hin presently.
